1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,880
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,880 --> 00:00:07,080
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:07,080 --> 00:00:08,120
And my name is Kathryn.
我是Kathryn。

4
00:00:08,120 --> 00:00:12,680
And today we're talking about office stuff, things in your office.
今天我们要聊聊办公室里的那些事儿，也就是你办公室里的东西。

5
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:13,680
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:19,640
We are talking about secrets in the office or maybe specific little things that people
我们要聊的是办公室里的秘密，或者说是人们

7
00:00:19,640 --> 00:00:22,200
talk about behind other people's back.
在背后议论的一些小事。

8
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:23,400
Okay, bad things then.
好吧，那就是些不好的事情了。

9
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,560
So this is an elementary level lesson.
这是一节初级课程。

10
00:00:25,560 --> 00:00:32,360
Before we get going though, let's take a look at a phrase in today's vocabulary preview.
不过在我们开始之前，先来看看今天词汇预览中的一个短语。

11
00:00:32,360 --> 00:00:33,360
Vocabulary preview.
词汇预览。

12
00:00:33,360 --> 00:00:34,560
All right.
好的。

13
00:00:34,560 --> 00:00:40,000
So the phrase for today is actually the same as the title for this lesson and that's office
今天的短语实际上和这节课的标题一样，就是办公室

14
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,000
gossip.
八卦。

15
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:43,160
Okay, you all know what an office is.
好吧，大家都知道办公室是什么。

16
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:44,660
What is gossip?
那八卦是什么呢？

17
00:00:44,660 --> 00:00:52,740
So to gossip means to talk about other people secretly or behind their backs or maybe talk
八卦的意思就是偷偷地或在背后议论别人，或者谈论

18
00:00:52,740 --> 00:00:56,680
about other people's problems or private things.
别人的问题或私事。

19
00:00:56,680 --> 00:00:59,680
So oh my God, did you hear?
所以，哦，天哪，你听说了吗？

20
00:00:59,680 --> 00:01:02,320
John is totally going to break up with her.
John 完全要和她分手了。

21
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:05,720
So you're talking about people without them knowing.
所以你是在别人不知情的情况下谈论他们。

22
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:06,720
Right.
没错。

23
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:10,960
So you're talking about their private things, their relationships, maybe you're even maybe
所以你是在谈论他们的私事、他们的关系，甚至可能还在

24
00:01:10,960 --> 00:01:12,480
criticizing them.
批评他们。

25
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:13,480
That's right.
对。

26
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:17,840
So office gossip is talking about people in your office without them knowing.
所以办公室八卦就是在同事不知情的情况下谈论他们。

27
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:19,760
So saying bad things about them.
就是说他们的坏话。

28
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:20,760
Right.
对。

29
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:26,160
So without any more delay, why don't we listen to this dialogue for the first time.
那就不多说了，我们先来听一遍这段对话吧。

30
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:30,320
Hey, Eric, have you heard?
嘿，埃里克，你听说了吗？

31
00:01:30,320 --> 00:01:32,920
No, go on.
没有，快说。

32
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:34,520
Tell me.
告诉我。

33
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:38,560
What's the latest office gossip?
最近有什么办公室八卦？

34
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:49,960
Well, you didn't hear this from me, but the rumor is Paula is getting a promotion.
嗯，你可别说是从我这儿听说的，但传闻是宝拉要升职了。

35
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:50,960
No way.
不可能。

36
00:01:50,960 --> 00:01:54,400
But she's a terrible worker and you can't trust her.
但她工作表现很差，而且你没法信任她。

37
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,400
She's so two faced.
她太两面三刀了。

38
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:57,200
You can't believe anything she says.
她说什么都不能信。

39
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:59,680
Hey guys, what are you two whispering about?
嘿，你们俩在嘀咕什么呢？

40
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:01,920
Oh, hi, Paula.
哦，嗨，宝拉。

41
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:02,920
How are you?
你好吗？

42
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:04,400
I've got some good news.
我有好消息。

43
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:05,400
I'm getting a promotion.
我要升职了。

44
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,400
Congratulations.
恭喜你。

45
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:11,000
Eric and I were just saying that you were the best person for the job.
埃里克和我刚才还在说你是最适合这个职位的人。

46
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:20,840
Yes, you're the best.
是啊，你是最棒的。

47
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:21,840
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

48
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:26,600
So we have four key words that we want to look at from this gossip dialogue.
所以，从这个八卦对话中，我们要看四个关键词。

49
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:32,120
So why don't we take a look at those now in Language Takeaway.
那我们不如在“语言要点”环节来看看这些词。

50
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:33,520
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

51
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:37,840
Okay, the first word is rumor.
好的，第一个词是“rumor”。

52
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:39,640
Rumor.
谣言。

53
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:42,000
Now this is an interesting word about gossip.
这是一个关于八卦的有趣词。

54
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,280
Yeah, a rumor.
是的，谣言。

55
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:47,320
So a rumor is a story that might or might not be true.
所以谣言是一个可能真实也可能不真实的故事。

56
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:48,320
Right.
对。

57
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:50,760
Okay, so I heard a rumor that they broke up yesterday.
好的，我听到一个谣言说他们昨天分手了。

58
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:56,080
Okay, so you're not sure if they broke up or no one has told you for a fact.
好的，所以你不确定他们是否分手了，或者没人确切告诉你。

59
00:02:56,080 --> 00:03:00,400
No, it means I probably heard it from someone else who heard it from someone else who heard
不，这意味着我可能是从别人那里听说的，那个人又从另一个人那里听说的，那个人又

60
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:03,240
it from someone else who doesn't really know.
从另一个不太了解情况的人那里听说的。

61
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:04,240
Right.
没错。

62
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:07,920
So rumors are maybe guesses about people and you don't know if they're true.
所以，谣言大概就是关于别人的猜测，你不知道它们是不是真的。

63
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:10,640
You see this a lot with famous people, movie stars.
你在名人、电影明星身上经常看到这种情况。

64
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:14,760
They always talk about rumors that maybe they got married in secret or something.
他们总是谈论谣言，比如他们可能秘密结婚了之类的。

65
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:15,760
Exactly.
正是。

66
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:18,880
There's a rumor that Angelina Jolie and Brad Pitt are breaking up.
有传言说安吉丽娜·朱莉和布拉德·皮特要分手了。

67
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:19,880
Right.
对。

68
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:21,720
Okay, so we don't know if it's true.
好吧，所以我们不知道这是不是真的。

69
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:22,720
Rumor.
谣言。

70
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:23,720
That's a rumor.
那就是个谣言。

71
00:03:23,720 --> 00:03:29,200
So now the rumor that they heard was that this girl Paula is getting a promotion.
所以他们听到的谣言是，这个叫宝拉的女孩要升职了。

72
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:30,320
Promotion.
升职。

73
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:32,560
This is an important office word.
这是个重要的办公室用语。

74
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:37,080
This means to be offered a better job in your company.
这意味着在公司里得到一个更好的职位。

75
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:38,200
That means to move up.
也就是往上走。

76
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:39,200
To move up.
往上走。

77
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:40,200
Right.
没错。

78
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,200
Alright, so this is a noun.
好了，所以这是个名词。

79
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,920
You get a promotion, right?
你得到升职，对吧？

80
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:47,400
Yes, I got a promotion last year which also meant I got more money.
是的，我去年升职了，这也意味着我涨了工资。

81
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,540
Okay, awesome.
好的，太棒了。

82
00:03:48,540 --> 00:03:50,640
So that is a promotion.
所以那就是升职。

83
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:56,880
Now when they were talking about the promotion, the girl said, I can't believe, the guy said,
当他们谈论升职时，那个女孩说“我简直不敢相信”，那个男的说，

84
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:59,600
and Eric said, I can't believe she's getting a promotion.
埃里克说：“我简直不敢相信她要升职了。”

85
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:01,600
She's so two-faced.
她太两面三刀了。

86
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,280
Two-faced.
两面三刀。

87
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,920
So think about what this means.
所以想想这是什么意思。

88
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,080
To have two faces.
有两张脸。

89
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:10,080
To be two-faced means to have two different sides to your personality.
两面三刀意味着你的性格有两面。

90
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:13,080
A good one and a bad one.
一面好，一面坏。

91
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:15,840
So like, I can be very nice to Marco.
比如，我可以对马可非常友好。

92
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:17,840
Marco, wow, you look so good today.
马可，哇，你今天看起来真棒。

93
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:18,840
You're such a nice guy.
你真是个好人。

94
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:19,840
You're such a hard worker.
你工作真努力。

95
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:22,560
And then, oh my God, Marco's such an idiot.
然后，哦天哪，马可真是个白痴。

96
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:25,160
He's like never working and he's always on the phone.
他好像从不工作，总在打电话。

97
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,160
Oh, hi Marco.
哦，嗨，马可。

98
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:27,160
How are you doing?
你好吗？

99
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,160
That is two-faced.
那就是两面三刀。

100
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:29,160
That's very good.
那很好。

101
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:32,440
Alright, so two-faced means to have two different sides to your personality.
好了，所以两面三刀意味着你的性格有两面。

102
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:37,080
Now it's interesting the way that you use this word, you say two-faced, right?
有趣的是，这个词的用法是你说“two-faced”，对吧？

103
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:38,920
So you have to add the E-D at the end.
所以你得在末尾加上“-ed”。

104
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:40,600
You can't say he is two-faced.
你不能说“he is two-faced”。

105
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,600
No.
不。

106
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:42,600
Or he has two-face.
或者“he has two-face”。

107
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,280
No, it's an adjective.
不，它是一个形容词。

108
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:45,280
So he's two-faced.
所以是“he's two-faced”。

109
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:46,280
Okay.
好的。

110
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,280
She is two-faced.
她是两面三刀的。

111
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:48,360
Okay, two-faced.
好的，两面三刀。

112
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:50,440
I don't like people who are two-faced.
我不喜欢两面三刀的人。

113
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:52,480
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

114
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:58,080
And we have one final word and it's actually a verb when people talk like this.
我们还有一个词，实际上是一个动词，当人们这样说话时。

115
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,080
When they're talking like this.
当他们这样说话时。

116
00:04:59,080 --> 00:05:00,080
So they're talking quietly.
所以他们小声说话。

117
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:01,080
Very quietly.
非常小声。

118
00:05:01,080 --> 00:05:02,080
To whisper.
耳语。

119
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:03,080
To whisper.
耳语。

120
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,080
Okay.
好的。

121
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:05,080
So what are you whispering about?
所以你们在耳语什么？

122
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:06,080
Uh-oh.
哦哦。

123
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:09,480
So usually when people are whispering, they're talking about a rumor.
所以通常当人们耳语时，他们在谈论谣言。

124
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:10,480
Right.
对。

125
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:11,480
Or they're talking in secret.
或者他们在秘密交谈。

126
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:13,080
You don't want somebody else to hear you.
你不想让别人听到。

127
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:14,080
Right.
对。

128
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:18,080
So when you want to be very quiet, like at the movie theater, you whisper.
所以当你想非常安静时，比如在电影院，你就耳语。

129
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,080
Whisper.
耳语。

130
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:20,080
Okay.
好的。

131
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:22,000
So those are four words for language takeaway.
所以这是语言学习的四个词。

132
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:26,480
Why don't we go back, listen to the dialogue again and we'll be back to take a look at
我们为什么不回去，再听一遍对话，然后回来看看

133
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:32,480
a couple of phrases.
几个短语。

134
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:33,480
Psst.
嘘。

135
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:34,480
Psst.
嘘。

136
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:37,480
Hey, Eric, have you heard?
嘿，埃里克，你听说了吗？

137
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,480
No.
没有。

138
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,480
Go on, tell me.
说吧，告诉我。

139
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,000
What's the latest office gossip?
办公室最近有什么八卦？

140
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:48,680
Well, you didn't hear this from me, but the rumor is Paula is getting a promotion.
嗯，你可别说是从我这儿听说的，但谣言是宝拉要升职了。

141
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:49,840
No way.
不可能。

142
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:53,080
But she's a terrible worker and you can't trust her.
但她工作很差劲，而且你不能信任她。

143
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:54,080
She's so two-faced.
她太两面三刀了。

144
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:56,880
You can't believe anything she says.
她说的任何话你都不能信。

145
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:59,280
Hey guys, what are you two whispering about?
嘿，你们俩在嘀咕什么呢？

146
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:01,840
Oh, hi Paula.
哦，嗨，宝拉。

147
00:06:01,840 --> 00:06:02,840
How are you?
你好吗？

148
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:04,320
I've got some good news.
我有好消息。

149
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:05,320
I'm getting a promotion.
我要升职了。

150
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:06,320
Congratulations.
恭喜。

151
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:10,960
Eric and I were just saying that you were the best person for the job.
埃里克和我刚才还在说你是最适合这个职位的人。

152
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:13,640
Yes, you're the best.
是的，你是最棒的。

153
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:16,840
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

154
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:23,480
So now we have three key phrases from this great dialogue on Fluency Builder.
所以现在我们从这段精彩的对话中得到了三个关键短语，用于流利度训练。

155
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:24,600
Fluency Builder.
流利度训练。

156
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:28,800
So this first one is the beginning to any great rumor.
所以第一个是任何大谣言的开始。

157
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,640
We say, have you heard?
我们说：“你听说了吗？”

158
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:31,640
Right.
对。

159
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:32,920
So, have you heard?
所以，你听说了吗？

160
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:35,040
Have you heard that she got a promotion?
你听说她升职了吗？

161
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,040
Right.
没错。

162
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:38,880
It's kind of, you're not really asking, right?
这有点像，你其实不是在问问题，对吧？

163
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:40,360
Although it is a question, have you heard?
虽然这是个问句，“你听说了吗？”

164
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:44,320
But you're not really expecting an answer.
但你并不真的期待一个回答。

165
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:47,280
This means I'm going to tell you some gossip.
这意味着我要告诉你一些八卦。

166
00:06:47,280 --> 00:06:48,280
Right.
没错。

167
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:49,520
Have you heard?
你听说了吗？

168
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:52,280
Because maybe I did, maybe I didn't, but I'm still going to say it.
因为也许我听说了，也许没有，但我还是会说出来。

169
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:53,600
I'm still going to say it anyway.
我还是会说出来，不管怎样。

170
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:56,520
So usually you can say, what?
所以通常你可以说，什么？

171
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:59,280
Or in this case, Eric goes, no, go on, tell me.
或者在这个例子里，埃里克说，不，说吧，告诉我。

172
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:00,920
What's the latest office gossip?
办公室里最新的八卦是什么？

173
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:03,960
So obviously he knows it's going to be gossip.
所以很明显他知道这会是八卦。

174
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:04,960
Right.
没错。

175
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:05,960
Have you heard?
你听说了吗？

176
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:06,960
All right.
好吧。

177
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:10,880
